Custom.definition: a practice common to many or to a particular place or institution ;esp

1.definition: a practice common to many or to a particular place or institutiona long-established practice that is generally recognized as having the force of law see alsocompare

sub_terms.a: duties, tolls, or imposts imposed by the law of a country on imports or exports
sub_terms.b: the agency, establishment, or procedure for collecting such customs
